        <h1>LeetCode 1855: Maximum Distance Between a Pair of Values (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given two non-increasing arrays a and b. Find the maximum distance between indices i and j such
                that i &lt; j and a[i] &lt;= b[j]. The distance is defined as j - i.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: a = [55,1,100], b = [1,77,100]<br>
                Output: 2<br>
                Explanation: For i=0, j=2: a[0]=55 &lt;= b[2]=100 and distance is 2-0=2. For i=1, j=2: a[1]=1 &lt;=
                b[2]=100 and distance is 2-1=1. Maximum is 2.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int maxDistance(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; a, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; b) {
        int i = 0, j = 0, res = 0;
        while (i &lt; a.size() &amp;&amp; j &lt; b.size()) {
            if (b[j] &gt;= a[i]) {
                res = max(res, j - i); // valid, move j
                j++;
            } else {
                i++; 
                j++; // shift both to keep j &gt;= i
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
